15:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Jasper and Surfer share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Seo Tools, Multilingual, Api Access. Where Jasper pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Short Form and Templates and Tone Control and Plagiarism Check, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Jasper holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Surfer scores 8/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
16:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Jasper offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $49/mo, compared to Surfer's starting price of $89/mo. Neither platform offers a free plan, so you will need to budget for at least the starting tier from the beginning. Be sure to take advantage of any trial periods they may offer."}]]}]
