19:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Jasper is best suited for marketing teams, ad copy, brand voice content, campaigns, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Surfer, meanwhile, shines for SEO optimization, content scoring, keyword research, content strategy, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Jasper describes itself as \"Enterprise AI marketing platform for brand-consistent content.\" Surfer, established in 2017, positions itself as \"Data-driven SEO content optimization and writing platform.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
1a:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Jasper** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 6), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Surfer is a poor choice — far from it. Surfer excels in its own right, particularly for SEO optimization and content scoring.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value 50+ templates for marketing use cases, go with Jasper. If best-in-class content scoring against serp competitors matters more to you, Surfer is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
